---
// Hierarchy section — addresses pre-launch peer feedback §9
// (hierarchy benefit buried). Two-column desktop layout:
//   Left  = prose on hierarchy + the open-questions-roll-up mechanic.
//   Right = an actual abbreviated tree from specscore-cli/spec/features/cli/
//           as a styled <pre> block.
// The "See it live →" link points at Studio so the reader can browse
// the real tree instead of trusting the abbreviated render.
//
// Pre-Habr scope: English only. RU + 6 other locales follow in a
// separate pass.
---

<section class="hierarchy section" aria-labelledby="hierarchy-title">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="hierarchy__grid">
      <div class="hierarchy__col hierarchy__col--text">
        <h2 id="hierarchy-title" class="hierarchy__title">
          Specs are hierarchical. So your spec tree is too.
        </h2>
        <p class="hierarchy__lead">
          Flat list at fifty Features becomes a dump. SpecScore keeps the
          tree navigable: parents own scope, children own detail, and the
          directory shape mirrors the product shape your team already
          reasons about.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Open questions roll up.</strong> Unresolved questions at
          any depth surface in every parent's index. You see what is
          blocking a release from the top of the tree, without spelunking
          to find it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most spec tools assume a flat list works. It does — until it
          doesn't. SpecScore is built for the moment when "where does
          this Feature live?" starts to matter.
        </p>
        <p class="hierarchy__cta">
          <a
            href="https://specscore.studio/app/github.com/specscore/specscore-cli/spec/features/cli?op=explore"
            class="hierarchy__live"
          >
            See it live in <code>specscore-cli</code> →
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure
        class="hierarchy__col hierarchy__col--tree"
        aria-label="An abbreviated view of the specscore CLI feature tree, showing parent features with their child sub-features and one sub-sub-feature beneath spec/lint/."
      >
        <figcaption class="hierarchy__caption">
          <span class="hierarchy__caption-label">FROM</span>
          <code>specscore-cli/spec/features/cli/</code>
        </figcaption>
<pre class="hierarchy__tree"><code><span class="hx-root">spec/features/cli/</span>
├── <span class="hx-dir">agent/</span>
│   └── <span class="hx-dir">setup/</span>
├── <span class="hx-dir">feature/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">change-status/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">deps/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">info/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">list/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">new/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">refs/</span>
│   └── <span class="hx-dir">tree/</span>
├── <span class="hx-dir">idea/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">change-status/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">new/</span>
│   └── <span class="hx-dir">relocate/</span>
├── <span class="hx-dir">spec/</span>
│   └── <span class="hx-dir">lint/</span>
│       ├── <span class="hx-dir">issue-rules/</span>     <span class="hx-annot">← sub-sub-Feature</span>
│       └── <span class="hx-dir">plan-rules/</span>
├── <span class="hx-dir">task/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">info/</span>
│   ├── <span class="hx-dir">list/</span>
│   └── <span class="hx-dir">new/</span>
└── <span class="hx-more">… 10 more top-level Features</span></code></pre>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hierarchy { background: var(--cream); }

  .hierarchy__title {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 22ch;
  }

  .hierarchy__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .hierarchy__grid {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
      gap: var(--space-5);
    }
  }
  .hierarchy__col { min-width: 0; }

  .hierarchy__lead {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
  .hierarchy__col--text p {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
  .hierarchy__col--text strong { color: var(--ink); }

  .hierarchy__cta { margin-top: var(--space-3); }
  .hierarchy__live {
    color: var(--ink-blue);
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;
  }
  .hierarchy__live code {
    font-family: inherit;
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .hierarchy__col--tree {
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    background: var(--surface);
  }
  .hierarchy__caption {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.875rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    background: var(--cream-2);
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .hierarchy__caption-label {
    color: var(--graphite);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .hierarchy__caption code {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    font-family: inherit;
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .hierarchy__tree {
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--space-3);
    background: var(--surface);
    border: none;
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-code);
  }
  .hx-root { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; }
  .hx-dir  { color: var(--ink); }
  .hx-annot {
    color: var(--ink-blue);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .hx-more {
    color: var(--pale-ink);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .hierarchy__tree { font-size: 0.78rem; }
  }
</style>
